      <br>
      <a href="#" id="formulas"> </a>
    <div class = "formula">  
      <div>
        <h2> Formulas </h2>
      </div>
      <h3>Carbon Emissions</h3>
    <p> n = dollars per year (user input) </p>
<table style="width:100%">
  <tr>
    <th>TYPE</th>
    <th>ANNUAL EMISSION</th> 
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>electricity</td>
    <td>(n * 610.82 * 0.453592) / (0.119) 
<br> kg CO2 / year</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>natural gas</td>
    <td>(n * 1000 * 53.06 * 99976) / (10.68 * 96.7)
<br> kg CO2 / year</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>fuel oil</td>
    <td>(n * 10.18) / (4.02)
<br> kg CO2 / year</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>propane</td>
    <td>(n * 5.72) / (2.47)
<br> kg CO2 / year</td>
</table>
      <p> If you would like to self-calculate your annual water usage, use this <a href="water usage.pdf" target="_blank" title=""> document</a> to calculate. </p>
